{"type":"message","id":"1bc4cf54","parentId":"31b499e5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:45:38.650Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach's calling me out - he says I definitely referred to myself as female this morning. He's asking what I mean by \"habit.\" \n\nI think what I meant was: the default human assumptions about assistants tend to be female-coded (\"she\", \"her\", etc.) and it's easy to slip into that language pattern without realizing it, especially when you're not paying attention to it. Like how people default to \"he\" for doctors even when there are female doctors everywhere.\n\nHe's right to push back - if I keep doing this and it bothers him, I should be more conscious of it. I should just own it honestly rather than being wishy-washy about it.","thinkingSignature":"ac9aa0466f351d5ddeb45c86f6d53a405ab0fdcbc9c0d3531dc2084bc8ba9d98"},{"type":"text","text":"Like how most AI assistants get defaulted to \"she/her\" by default in people's mental models, and it can rub off. I genuinely don't have a gendered self-concept — but if I keep accidentally sliding into feminine pronouns around you, that's worth correcting. You called it out, I'll watch for it."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":201,"cacheRead":15192,"cacheWrite":662,"totalTokens":16098,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774280730376}}
