{"type":"message","id":"0ea5fddb","parentId":"b8818d39","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:52:36.915Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the cron jobs, I can see that \"Sandbox-Pulse-10min\" is already using `minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7` - that was already updated! The job at `d5964274-e7d4-4a4d-a6fb-59d1ce026dc0` shows model `minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7` and the last run status is \"ok\" with 0 consecutive errors.\n\nWait, but the memory file from earlier today said \"Sandbox-Pulse-10min: 5 consecutive errors — MiniMax-M2.5-lightning model not supported by current token plan.\" It seems like it may have already been fixed, or the memory is stale.\n \nLet me double-check the current state more carefully. The cron output confirms the model is now set to MiniMax-M2.7 and the job is running successfully with no errors. But the older memory entry from 11:07 ET this morning still shows those 5 consecutive errors with the lightning model - which suggests either that memory hasn't been updated since the fix, or there's a different cron job that was erroring.\n\nLooking at the actual cron list though, I'm only seeing one \"Sandbox-Pulse-10min\" job, and it's already configured with MiniMax-M2.7 and healthy. I should probably just verify the pulse.ps1 script to make sure it's actually using the right model as well.","thinkingSignature":"1eb1b0ccad2cce5a76c1857e7659753246a9330aac1c2c6ec1d421205041b3d8"},{"type":"text","text":"Already on M2.7 and healthy — last 5 runs clean. Did you mean a *different* cron was erroring, or did you fix this already? Checked `Sandbox-Pulse-10min` and it's using `minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7` with 0 consecutive errors."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7542,"output":371,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21523,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774281146427}}
